{"page_id": 43, "full_text": {"audio_url": "https://storage.googleapis.com/cloud_storage_leturn/Ch4_part1.pdf/Ch4_part1_audio_folder/43/Ch4_part1_full_audio_43.mp3", "full_text": "Marginalization\n\u25aa Let X be a random variable whose possible values are {x1, x2}\n\u25aa Let Y be a random variable whose possible values are {y1, y2 , y3}\n\u25aa Then, we can obtain P(X) and P(Y) from P(X, Y) as follows:\n\u2013 P(X) = P(X, Y = y1) + P(X, Y = y2) + P(X, Y = y3) (Y is marginalized out)\n\u2013 P(Y) = P(X = x1, Y) + P(X = x2, Y) (X is marginalized out)\n\u25aa Example\nX = x1\n0.2\n0.3\n0.05\nX = x2\n0.1\n0.2\n0.15\nY = y1\nY = y2\nY = y3\nP(Y = y2) = P(X = x1, Y = y2) + P(X = x2, Y = y2) = 0.5\nP(X = x1) = P(X = x1, Y = y1) + P(X = x1, Y = y2) + P(X = x1, Y = y3) = 0.55\n43\n"}, "text": [{"audio_url": "https://storage.googleapis.com/cloud_storage_leturn/Ch4_part1.pdf/Ch4_part1_audio_folder/43/Ch4_part1_audio_43_1.mp3", "font_size": 32, "text": "Marginalization\n"}, {"audio_url": "https://storage.googleapis.com/cloud_storage_leturn/Ch4_part1.pdf/Ch4_part1_audio_folder/43/Ch4_part1_audio_43_2.mp3", "font_size": 24, "text": "\u25aa Let X be a random variable whose possible values are {x1, x2}\n\u25aa Let Y be a random variable whose possible values are {y1, y2 , y3}\n\u25aa Then, we can obtain P(X) and P(Y) from P(X, Y) as follows:\n"}, {"audio_url": "https://storage.googleapis.com/cloud_storage_leturn/Ch4_part1.pdf/Ch4_part1_audio_folder/43/Ch4_part1_audio_43_3.mp3", "font_size": 20, "text": "\u2013 P(X) = P(X, Y = y1) + P(X, Y = y2) + P(X, Y = y3) (Y is marginalized out)\n\u2013 P(Y) = P(X = x1, Y) + P(X = x2, Y) (X is marginalized out)\n"}, {"audio_url": "https://storage.googleapis.com/cloud_storage_leturn/Ch4_part1.pdf/Ch4_part1_audio_folder/43/Ch4_part1_audio_43_4.mp3", "font_size": 24, "text": "\u25aa Example\n"}, {"audio_url": "https://storage.googleapis.com/cloud_storage_leturn/Ch4_part1.pdf/Ch4_part1_audio_folder/43/Ch4_part1_audio_43_5.mp3", "font_size": 12, "